![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/8b0b93dd-719f-4db7-a53a-30acb701a78f/46911.jpg?format=original)

Speaking in a recent interview on the Hits Radio Breakfast Show alongside Anne Hathaway and Emily Blunt during “The Devil Wears Prada 2” press tour, Meryl Streep criticized what she described as a growing reliance on clear-cut heroes and villains in contemporary movies.

“I think we tend to Marvel-ize the movies now. We got the villains and we got the good guys, and it’s so boring. What’s really interesting about life is that some of the heroes are flawed and some of the villains are human and interesting and have their own strengths. So that’s what I like about \[‘Devil Wears Prada 2’\]. It’s messier.”

While there's a point to what she is saying and it is absolutely a valid one. Marvel fans will have something to say about her apparent characterization of the heroes and villains in the MCU